- the financial officer has proved the inaccuracy of the information reported by the taxman in the ZM or the correction ZM.
The correction received by the financial officer, without a correction ZM being made by the tax officer, does not replace the tax inspector's right to make a correction ZM, but only leads to the correction of the data in the MIAS, so that it is current, complete and accurate.
The ZM data will be sent to the Member States concerned.
Only the national financial authority designated for cooperation with the other Member States in the field of turnover tax may transmit and receive this data.
This is the CLO (in the Czech Republic this function is performed by the Department of International Mutual Assistance in the field of VAT in the Ministry of Finance) and the message "O _ MCTL" automatically receives the CLO from the other Member States.
It contains all incorrect USt-IdNr., which were specified in the transmitted ZM lines.
If the incorrect VAT ID number is used in some of the transmitted lines of the ZM or the corrected ZM, an entry will be made in the wrong VAT ID list.
