International exchange of information without prior request is either automatic, structured or in the form of instant information.
Information is often provided to financial officials in other Member States without any prior request, which is important for fixing the value added tax debt.
In the Czech Republic, all information is collected by the CLO.
The exchange of information between the individual Member States takes place electronically.
According to Council Regulation (EC) No 1798 / 2003, "automatic exchange" means the systematic transmission of previously defined information to other Member States at regular, predetermined intervals without any prior request.
"Structured automatic exchange" means the systematic transfer of previously defined information to another Member State without its prior request as soon as the information in question is available.
The Czech Republic informs the other Member States in the automatic exchange of information on deliveries of new vehicles.
The financial officer obtains this information from the form of notification of the delivery of a new vehicle in accordance with Section 19 of Law 235 / 2004 and from the copy of the invoice issued.
When processing this form, the financial officer will provide the required data in the document and forward it directly to the responsible representative of the Finance Directorate, where these data will be collected and sent to the CLO for further processing, after which the data will be transmitted to the other Member States within the specified period, at the latest within two months of the end of the quarter in which they were obtained.
The Czech Republic also provides information to other Member States on mail order transactions that are tax-free in the country of origin, intra-Community transactions that appear inadmissible and potential "missing traders."
This information is transmitted to other Member States by means of a SCAC pre-print in a spontaneous exchange of information.
