VAT risk management
Risk management in the Czech Republic
In the Czech Republic, several organizational units at different levels of financial management are involved in risk management in the area of sales tax.
Within the Czech Ministry of Finance, the following organisational units are responsible for risk management and the fight against VAT fraud:
The department for methodology and economic management of sales tax or its unit for risk management deals with the identification of potential risk areas for tax revenue and evaluates the trends in these risks in domestic and intra-Community trade.
At the national level, this body coordinates the requirements for the criterion of "credibility of VAT returns" and uses the MIAS data to discover possible tax evasion within the framework of intra-Community deliveries and purchases.
Based on data on the trade balance of the Czech Republic, it evaluates high-risk products, prepares the risk management in the area of turnover tax in a conceptual manner and cooperates in this area with the competent EC institutions and the other Member States.
The department for international mutual assistance in the field of VAT provides inter alia for the exchange of information, participates in the creation and implementation of a relevant information database, evaluates the data of other Member States available in the MIAS system, carries out public relations work and is responsible for other forms of intergovernmental assistance within the meaning of Council Regulation (EC) 1798 / 2003.
